13/05/2008
SKOPJE, Macedonia â The US Embassy in Macedonia is urging authorities to investigate incidents that marred the official start of campaigning Sunday (May 11th).
In a statement Monday, the embassy in Skopje stressed that successful elections are vital to Macedonia's future.
In one case, two men fired at Democratic Union for Integration (DUI) leader Ali Ahmeti's vehicle during his visit to Bogovinje.
He escaped injury.
Police arrested one suspect.
There were also several separate attacks against offices of the DUI and of the Democratic Party of Albanians.
